00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:47,850
He wasn't abroad.

269
00:18:47,850 --> 00:18:50,950
I heard he took a year off because he was sick.

270
00:18:50,950 --> 00:18:53,460
You know we're getting
a grass lawn outside, right?

271
00:18:53,460 --> 00:18:55,840
Hae's family is paying for it.

272
00:19:07,390 --> 00:19:09,390
 

273
00:19:13,260 --> 00:19:16,290
His family is paying for the lawn?

274
00:19:37,590 --> 00:19:39,130
Hey.

275
00:19:39,130 --> 00:19:40,930
I'm the class president.

276
00:19:42,130 --> 00:19:44,630
I have your prize certificate and gift card.

277
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:48,460
You waited for me because of this?

278
00:19:52,230 --> 00:19:54,200
I thought I might miss you if I came after dinner.

279
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:58,120
Our teacher says to fill out the career
aspiration form inside the envelope.

280
00:19:58,120 --> 00:20:00,500
Who is this?

281
00:20:00,500 --> 00:20:02,940
Do I need to say hello?

282
00:20:04,790 --> 00:20:06,610
Hello.

283
00:20:06,610 --> 00:20:08,310
I'm the class president.

284
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:11,260
I'm running an errand.

285
00:20:11,260 --> 00:20:13,230
Hello.

286
00:20:13,230 --> 00:20:14,990
I'm his sister.

287
00:20:14,990 --> 00:20:17,660
I go to daycare.

288
00:20:19,780 --> 00:20:21,670
Want ramen?

289
00:20:23,740 --> 00:20:25,420
Ramen?

290
00:20:27,610 --> 00:20:30,010
Thank you for the food.

291
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:41,400
- So good.
- I make good ramen.

292
00:20:49,810 --> 00:20:53,610
It's just one pebble that fell in,

293
00:20:53,610 --> 00:20:56,490
but everything spilled out.

294
00:21:24,100 --> 00:21:27,210
It's been so long since I read
a novel that wasn't on an exam.

295
00:21:27,210 --> 00:21:28,300
It's so good.

296
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:30,500
- Is it good?
- I'm hard to please.

297
00:21:30,500 --> 00:21:34,900
Everything they told me to read
since I was little was no fun.

298
00:21:37,030 --> 00:21:41,050
If you like it, do you want to borrow it?

299
00:21:42,810 --> 00:21:45,120
- Can I?
- It will be published soon.

300
00:21:45,120 --> 00:21:47,260
- Published?
- Yes.

301
00:21:47,260 --> 00:21:50,000
Wait, did you write this?

302
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:53,780
I wanted my sister to read,
but I didn't see anything I liked.

303
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:58,780
You did something amazing, like it was nothing.

304
00:21:58,780 --> 00:22:01,480
Are you a genius or something?

305
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,210
I don't know about that.

306
00:22:03,210 --> 00:22:04,980
I just want to make money.

307
00:22:04,980 --> 00:22:06,530
Money.

308
00:22:08,740 --> 00:22:12,970
I'll buy the book when it's out.

309
00:22:12,970 --> 00:22:17,760
If you want me to pay for the ramen, I will.

310
00:22:21,660 --> 00:22:23,920
She wanted this form from me?
 

311
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,240
How did she know I'm not going to school?

312
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:30,050
Why do you keep missing school?

313
00:22:30,050 --> 00:22:31,830
To work and sleep.

314
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:33,840
There's nothing for me to do there anyway.

315
00:22:33,840 --> 00:22:36,290
My future aspiration?

316
00:22:36,290 --> 00:22:37,900
George Clooney.

317
00:22:37,900 --> 00:22:40,360
What are you doing? Be serious.

318
00:22:40,360 --> 00:22:42,520
I am serious. It's just hard.

319
00:22:42,520 --> 00:22:45,430
That's the easiest thing in the world.

320
00:22:46,910 --> 00:22:50,100
Then, fill out the part about
what your parents want first.

321
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:56,020
 

322
00:22:57,230 --> 00:22:58,700
What did you write, Class President?

323
00:22:58,700 --> 00:23:01,320
Judge, prosecutor, lawyer.

324
00:23:01,320 --> 00:23:02,800
I wrote down what my mom said.

325
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,740
Aren't you supposed to write what you want?

326
00:23:04,740 --> 00:23:07,050
- You're not your mom.
- Geez.

327
00:23:07,050 --> 00:23:10,050
Let's see what you come up with, then.

328
00:23:12,700 --> 00:23:13,890
Sorry.

329
00:23:13,890 --> 00:23:18,400
We're not that close yet.

330
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,620
I got too riled up.

331
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:26,480
I'm just going to write "rich."

332
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,740
I want to be rich.

333
00:23:27,740 --> 00:23:30,000
Can you fill out all three choices?

334
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:34,700
Then, rich, billionaire, chaebol.

335
00:23:43,020 --> 00:23:44,560
Hey.

336
00:23:44,560 --> 00:23:48,010
So do you work part-time? Something like that?

337
00:23:48,010 --> 00:23:50,690
Yeah. When I'm awake, always.

338
00:23:50,690 --> 00:23:54,260
Can I ask you why?

339
00:23:54,260 --> 00:23:57,930
I don't know. To make a living, I guess?

340
00:23:57,930 --> 00:23:59,660
What do you do when you're awake?

341
00:23:59,660 --> 00:24:01,910
Except for when I'm sleeping, I study.

342
00:24:01,910 --> 00:24:05,080
Wow. Amazing.

343
00:24:05,080 --> 00:24:06,160
Isn't that exhausting?

344
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:08,250
Is it supposed to be?

345
00:24:08,250 --> 00:24:09,900
I don't know.

346
00:24:12,980 --> 00:24:15,880
I thought you were going to write down "actor."

347
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,190
That's nonsense.

348
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:18,720
For the career aspiration form.

349
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:21,970
When we were young, you were so famous.

350
00:24:21,970 --> 00:24:25,840
Did you retire or something like that?

351
00:24:25,840 --> 00:24:28,280
George Clooney is an actor, too.

352
00:24:29,900 --> 00:24:31,600
I didn't know.

353
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:34,050
I don't really watch TV.

354
00:24:34,050 --> 00:24:38,500
I guess that's why it sounded strange.

355
00:24:38,500 --> 00:24:40,040
It was a person.

356
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:42,760
You must not be online so much.

357
00:24:42,760 --> 00:24:45,780
Haven't you heard what kids say about me?

358
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:50,730
I'm not interested in other people's business.

359
00:24:51,810 --> 00:24:53,950
How about you sleep at school?

360
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:56,430
You can say you're sick
and sleep at the nurse's office.

361
00:24:56,430 --> 00:24:58,500
Or you can be late or go home early.

362
00:24:58,500 --> 00:25:01,130
- Get to the point.
- I'm worried about you.

363
00:25:01,130 --> 00:25:04,620
What if you don't have enough
attendance days to graduate?

364
00:25:04,620 --> 00:25:06,290
Wow.

365
00:25:06,290 --> 00:25:10,690
It's been so long since someone
else besides Geon No worried about me.

366
00:25:10,690 --> 00:25:12,850
Who's Geon No?

367
00:25:12,850 --> 00:25:16,000
If he's your hyung, he must be really old.

368
00:25:23,830 --> 00:25:24,970
Can you ring me up?

369
00:25:24,970 --> 00:25:27,210
One moment.

370
00:25:27,210 --> 00:25:29,600
- How was everything?
- Good.

371
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,790
One soju, one beer...

372
00:25:31,790 --> 00:25:34,770
47,000 won. Ow!

373
00:25:38,530 --> 00:25:40,160
- Would you like a receipt?
- No, thank you.

374
00:25:40,160 --> 00:25:43,130
Thank you... ow!

375
00:25:43,130 --> 00:25:45,450
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine. All good.

376
00:25:45,450 --> 00:25:46,530
Thank you. Come again.

377
00:25:46,530 --> 00:25:48,900
See you later.

378
00:25:50,360 --> 00:25:51,530
Bye.

379
00:25:51,530 --> 00:25:54,060
Hae, does this have to be here?
I keep getting poked.

380
00:25:54,060 --> 00:25:55,380
It looks nice here.

381
00:25:55,380 --> 00:25:58,380
It's been there forever.
You're still getting poked?

382
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:05,340
Here's your food that you didn't order.

383
00:26:05,340 --> 00:26:08,120
If I didn't order it, why am I getting it?

384
00:26:08,120 --> 00:26:11,010
Why are you only drinking then?

385
00:26:12,900 --> 00:26:14,770
A flower shop during the day and a bar at night?

386
00:26:14,770 --> 00:26:16,900
I've been helping out since I was 20.

387
00:26:16,900 --> 00:26:20,280
- We're from the same town.
- Since you were 20?

388
00:26:20,280 --> 00:26:23,660
Right, you were 20 when we were in 12th grade.

389
00:26:23,660 --> 00:26:25,960
You got held back because you were sick, right?

390
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:28,200
Did I even tell you that?

391
00:26:28,200 --> 00:26:30,250
The Class President knows it all.

392
00:26:30,250 --> 00:26:32,510
Don't act up.

393
00:26:32,510 --> 00:26:34,400
Got it, Class President.

394
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:35,830
Please eat.

395
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:41,160
Hey. I had this childish thought
for the first time back then.

396
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:44,900
When you would miss school because of work,

397
00:26:44,900 --> 00:26:47,060
the fact that you were making money for yourself

398
00:26:47,060 --> 00:26:49,390
seemed like such a foreign idea.

399
00:26:49,390 --> 00:26:52,070
It seemed so grown-up.

400
00:26:52,070 --> 00:26:55,470
Working to make ends meet and pay down debt?

401
00:26:55,470 --> 00:26:56,670
That does seem grown-up.

402
00:26:56,670 --> 00:27:00,420
Hey, why be so rude when I'm saying you were cool?

403
00:27:00,420 --> 00:27:02,400
Fine.

404
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:05,260
Just eat. It's really good. Eat.

405
00:27:05,260 --> 00:27:07,760
- Did you make it?
- Of course.

406
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:13,900
- It's tasty!
- I know.

407
00:27:14,900 --> 00:27:16,970
What drink should I pair it with?

408
00:27:16,970 --> 00:27:18,760
One second.

409
00:27:20,860 --> 00:27:22,670
Here.

410
00:27:22,670 --> 00:27:25,630
This one. See? The Boss himself-

411
00:27:25,630 --> 00:27:27,250
230,000 won?

412
00:27:27,250 --> 00:27:29,260
Did you forget you were treating?

413
00:27:29,260 --> 00:27:31,400
I acted like a server without
even thinking about it.

414
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:35,050
Fortunately, Geon No broke this bottle last time.

415
00:27:37,220 --> 00:27:38,900
- What? Fortunately?
- Fire!

416
00:27:38,900 --> 00:27:41,070
Oh, my gosh!

417
00:27:41,070 --> 00:27:42,920
Let me help you. One second.

418
00:27:42,920 --> 00:27:45,420
I've been waiting for this.

419
00:27:45,420 --> 00:27:47,460
I knew this would come in handy.

420
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:49,260
Excuse me!

421
00:27:49,260 --> 00:27:51,490
- Excuse me!
- Don't get close!

422
00:27:51,490 --> 00:27:55,130
Excuse me! Move out of the way!

423
00:27:56,650 --> 00:27:59,090
What are you doing?

424
00:27:59,090 --> 00:28:02,130
Hey! Careful!

425
00:28:13,460 --> 00:28:15,070
Wow, what was that?

426
00:28:15,070 --> 00:28:18,050
It went out right away. Are you a firefighter?

427
00:28:18,050 --> 00:28:20,220
Are you okay?

428
00:28:20,220 --> 00:28:22,730
Water would have worked just fine.

429
00:28:22,730 --> 00:28:25,440
That's your guest. You clean it up.

430
00:28:25,440 --> 00:28:28,460
This is our restaurant. Let's clean up together.

431
00:28:34,320 --> 00:28:36,240
So cool.

432
00:28:39,690 --> 00:28:42,870
Is it true that Sunwoo Hae goes to a motel?

433
00:28:42,870 --> 00:28:44,480
And he transferred to our school?

434
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,740
That hurts our school's reputation.

435
00:28:46,740 --> 00:28:49,300
Hey, did you get into college yet?

436
00:28:49,300 --> 00:28:50,900
Go gossip outside.

437
00:28:50,900 --> 00:28:55,100
Guys, let's be quiet. We're studying.

438
00:28:56,170 --> 00:28:58,240
Including you, Kim Seok Joo.

439
00:28:58,240 --> 00:28:59,400
Me?

440
00:28:59,400 --> 00:29:03,760
Also, spreading rumors is wrong.

441
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:05,530
Please stop.

442
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:11,900
If you keep missing school,
you might not graduate.

443
00:29:12,880 --> 00:29:15,670
Here are places you might apply
for special rolling admission.

444
00:29:15,670 --> 00:29:19,500
If you study, you could try for regular admission.

445
00:29:19,500 --> 00:29:23,180
Is it weird to go from troublemaker
to special student over a few awards?

446
00:29:23,180 --> 00:29:26,050
Coming here in the first place was cheating.

447
00:29:26,050 --> 00:29:28,570
You should cheat in life sometimes.

448
00:29:28,570 --> 00:29:31,200
You're allowed.

449
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:34,220
Also, what's with George Clooney?

450
00:29:34,220 --> 00:29:35,990
Will you change your name?

451
00:29:35,990 --> 00:29:38,840
Sunwoo... Clooney?

452
00:29:38,840 --> 00:29:40,440
Those are both surnames.

453
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:43,420
In Korean, it's like Sunwoo Namgung.

454
00:29:43,420 --> 00:29:46,500
Why am I even entertaining this?

455
00:29:52,530 --> 00:29:54,500
What did the Teacher say?

456
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:57,720
She wants me to try for rolling admission.
But why bother?

457
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:59,690
It's because your grades are crap, right?

458
00:29:59,690 --> 00:30:01,860
I know you don't study at all.

459
00:30:01,860 --> 00:30:04,500
I told you to pay attention to your attendance.

460
00:30:04,500 --> 00:30:07,990
That's true, but I'm not going to college.

461
00:30:07,990 --> 00:30:11,640
How can you not go to college?

462
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:14,030
Some people don't.

463
00:30:15,660 --> 00:30:18,610
Where are you going? It's lunch.

464
00:30:22,580 --> 00:30:25,110
Hey, run, run!

465
00:30:27,700 --> 00:30:29,800
- Hurry up!
- Here.

466
00:30:33,800 --> 00:30:35,770
For dessert.

467
00:30:36,770 --> 00:30:38,690
What?

468
00:30:38,690 --> 00:30:40,500
What is this candy?

469
00:30:40,500 --> 00:30:42,260
Wait for me!

470
00:30:54,950 --> 00:30:56,620
Is it good?

471
00:30:57,700 --> 00:31:01,780
It's suddenly good.

472
00:31:02,740 --> 00:31:04,670
How about you? Is it good?

473
00:31:04,670 --> 00:31:06,640
It's so sweet.

474
00:31:07,950 --> 00:31:10,930
Why aren't you eating lunch?

475
00:31:10,930 --> 00:31:12,500
I didn't pay for it. Didn't want to waste money.

476
00:31:12,500 --> 00:31:16,540
But the nutritionists worked
so hard to put it together.

477
00:31:16,540 --> 00:31:18,710
It's healthy...

478
00:31:18,710 --> 00:31:20,620
I see.

479
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:33,330
I think your idea was actually good.

480
00:31:33,330 --> 00:31:35,380
I'm going to use it more often.

481
00:31:35,380 --> 00:31:37,330
 

482
00:31:37,330 --> 00:31:40,650
 Oh, sleeping at the nurse's office? 

483
00:31:40,650 --> 00:31:42,040
Yes.

484
00:31:47,660 --> 00:31:49,630
Give it to your sister.

485
00:31:49,630 --> 00:31:50,950
Glow-in-the-dark stars?

486
00:31:50,950 --> 00:31:54,250
You can put them on the ceiling
or wherever your sister wants.

487
00:31:54,250 --> 00:31:56,680
Why didn't I think of this?

488
00:31:56,680 --> 00:31:58,530
Because I thought of it?

489
00:31:58,530 --> 00:32:01,200
How are you going to be rich like that?

490
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:04,840
Besides what your mom told you
to write, what do you want to be?

491
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,920
What?

492
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:08,130
Me?

493
00:32:09,090 --> 00:32:10,510
Going to Seoul National University?

494
00:32:10,510 --> 00:32:12,210
That's about going somewhere.

495
00:32:12,210 --> 00:32:14,470
My question was about your dream.

496
00:32:14,470 --> 00:32:16,600
Do you have to have a dream?

497
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:23,800
I'm curious about what kind
of dreams shining ones like you dream.

498
00:32:25,390 --> 00:32:27,340
Hey!

499
00:32:28,380 --> 00:32:31,430
Why would you say that?

500
00:32:33,020 --> 00:32:34,990
Are you okay?

501
00:32:41,740 --> 00:32:44,710
The sky is really pretty.

502
00:33:05,610 --> 00:33:07,370
 Focus! 

503
00:33:09,180 --> 00:33:10,410
I am focused.

504
00:33:10,410 --> 00:33:12,080
Bullshit.

505
00:33:20,830 --> 00:33:22,900
At least pretend like you're reading.

506
00:33:29,230 --> 00:33:33,030
Hae, I'm hearing a rumor.

507
00:33:35,560 --> 00:33:37,250
What is wrong with you?

508
00:33:37,250 --> 00:33:38,790
Listen to what he has to say.

509
00:33:38,790 --> 00:33:40,110
Motel?

510
00:33:40,110 --> 00:33:42,080
A student going to a motel?

511
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:45,600
I turned a blind eye to your issues
because of your special skills.

512
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:49,520
But I hear you walked out of a motel
behind City Hall with a woman.

513
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:51,490
The rumors are everywhere!

514
00:33:51,490 --> 00:33:53,500
How did anyone see? It must've been a customer.

515
00:33:53,500 --> 00:33:56,280
You should say sorry first!

516
00:33:56,280 --> 00:33:59,160
You are suspended.

517
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:01,510
You'd better stay home.

518
00:34:44,310 --> 00:34:46,560
What? You really came.

519
00:34:47,550 --> 00:34:49,470
Do you have a crush on Sunwoo Hae?

520
00:34:50,410 --> 00:34:52,490
Does Sunwoo Hae like you?

521
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:56,710
Do you have a crush on Sunwoo Hae?

522
00:34:56,710 --> 00:34:58,700
How did you know?

523
00:34:58,700 --> 00:35:00,610
- Don't be funny.
- Then, laugh.

524
00:35:00,610 --> 00:35:02,840
You haven't changed since you were a kid.

525
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:05,460
You have such a weird personality.

526
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:13,240
- Did you bring her?
- Is she someone who'd follow me?

527
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:15,190
Stop showing up where I am.

528
00:35:15,190 --> 00:35:18,060
I don't want your mom to think I lured you out.

529
00:35:18,060 --> 00:35:21,000
I wanted to see if the rumor was true.

530
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:22,370
You and the motel, Hyung.

531
00:35:22,370 --> 00:35:23,880
Why are you curious about that?

532
00:35:23,880 --> 00:35:26,180
I thought she might be.

533
00:35:28,000 --> 00:35:30,090
This is no fun.

534
00:35:30,090 --> 00:35:31,600
I'm leaving.

535
00:35:36,910 --> 00:35:39,030
I-I'm not curious.

536
00:35:39,030 --> 00:35:40,680
I trust you.

537
00:35:40,680 --> 00:35:43,080
I don't trust him.

