815
01:00:57,190 --> 01:00:58,660
Is our family in ruins?

816
01:00:58,660 --> 01:01:01,040
We're not.

817
01:01:01,040 --> 01:01:03,190
We're on our way, though.

818
01:01:03,190 --> 01:01:05,580
You need to focus on your exams, so we didn't-

819
01:01:05,580 --> 01:01:08,020
You want to drive this car while we're going down?

820
01:01:08,020 --> 01:01:10,020
I'm on my way to sell it!

821
01:01:12,070 --> 01:01:15,910
Dad will take care of it. Don't you worry.

822
01:01:15,910 --> 01:01:17,830
Focus on your business.

823
01:01:17,830 --> 01:01:20,810
Gosh, I am...

824
01:01:22,200 --> 01:01:25,160
How can we crumble overnight?

825
01:01:25,160 --> 01:01:28,650
If we're crumbling, you should have told me!

826
01:01:28,650 --> 01:01:32,450
I didn't want it to get in the way of your studies.

827
01:01:33,820 --> 01:01:35,500
Are you crying?

828
01:01:36,780 --> 01:01:38,780
Where are we at, exactly?

829
01:01:38,780 --> 01:01:40,820
I mean...

830
01:01:40,820 --> 01:01:44,160
if I had known that even yesterday,

831
01:01:44,160 --> 01:01:45,980
I would've told him we're in the same boat.

832
01:01:45,980 --> 01:01:49,830
I would have said I'm struggling, too.

833
01:01:51,300 --> 01:01:53,200
For real?

834
01:02:02,330 --> 01:02:05,690
 

835
01:02:08,680 --> 01:02:10,280
 

836
01:02:10,280 --> 01:02:12,410
 

837
01:02:12,410 --> 01:02:15,690
 

838
01:02:35,000 --> 01:02:37,760
It's a night for counting stars, Mother.

839
01:02:38,560 --> 01:02:41,260
I can't study at all.

840
01:02:59,790 --> 01:03:01,560
Hey!

841
01:03:01,560 --> 01:03:04,490
If you're here, come inside.

842
01:03:04,490 --> 01:03:06,240
You lied to me.

843
01:03:06,240 --> 01:03:07,770
The rumors are true.

844
01:03:07,770 --> 01:03:09,960
Motel! Woman!

845
01:03:11,210 --> 01:03:12,910
I'll be in when I handle this, Boss.

846
01:03:12,910 --> 01:03:14,380
Sure.

847
01:03:14,380 --> 01:03:16,300
Hurry up.

848
01:03:20,420 --> 01:03:22,490
The Boss must have a lot of money.

849
01:03:22,490 --> 01:03:24,700
Was that the money you didn't want to spend?

850
01:03:24,700 --> 01:03:26,400
Why her and not me?

851
01:03:26,400 --> 01:03:30,200
Did you study with a nosebleed just
so you can waste your energy here?

852
01:03:31,370 --> 01:03:33,880
How did you know I got a nosebleed?

853
01:03:35,210 --> 01:03:36,720
Damn it!

854
01:03:37,720 --> 01:03:39,010
You wouldn't even kiss me!

855
01:03:39,010 --> 01:03:42,060
If I kiss you or whatever,

856
01:03:42,060 --> 01:03:43,400
will you leave quietly?

857
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:46,930
I don't know! Unless you do it.

858
01:03:46,930 --> 01:03:49,080
Don't stop me this time.

859
01:04:01,760 --> 01:04:04,680
I can't study at all because of you.

860
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:07,580
All I write in my diary is your name.

861
01:04:07,580 --> 01:04:09,590
It's so annoying!

862
01:04:11,630 --> 01:04:14,430
That's the only thing you can't do?

863
01:04:14,430 --> 01:04:16,000
Studying?

864
01:04:16,000 --> 01:04:17,070
Only?

865
01:04:17,070 --> 01:04:18,900
Right now, my life depends on it.

866
01:04:18,900 --> 01:04:22,930
That's what I mean.
Live for that right now. Not me.

867
01:04:23,930 --> 01:04:27,280
Go home. Don't come back.

868
01:04:27,280 --> 01:04:29,720
You shouldn't be at a place like this.

869
01:04:34,660 --> 01:04:36,380
Hey.

870
01:04:36,380 --> 01:04:38,900
Don't act like you know me ever again!

871
01:04:38,900 --> 01:04:40,680
Forever!

872
01:05:00,720 --> 01:05:02,830
 

873
01:05:19,560 --> 01:05:21,230
It's sweet.

874
01:05:27,700 --> 01:05:33,610
Wow, you really bought enough
ice cream for yourself.

875
01:05:33,610 --> 01:05:36,050
I thought it would melt.

876
01:05:36,050 --> 01:05:38,390
You're working.

877
01:05:39,220 --> 01:05:41,990
Fine. Have plenty.

878
01:05:45,000 --> 01:05:49,500
We're all grown up and sharing drinks.

879
01:05:53,300 --> 01:05:56,060
Are we really all grown up?

880
01:05:56,060 --> 01:05:58,260
I'm all grown up.

881
01:05:58,260 --> 01:06:00,290
You're not, I guess.

882
01:06:06,690 --> 01:06:10,400
What happened with the TV program?

883
01:06:10,400 --> 01:06:12,240
Why do you want to know?

884
01:06:12,240 --> 01:06:13,800
It's not like you're going to do it.

885
01:06:13,800 --> 01:06:17,900
If you're casting it yourself,
it must be important to you.

886
01:06:22,870 --> 01:06:26,060
I didn't know you'd become a manager.

887
01:06:26,060 --> 01:06:31,160
I didn't know you'd become a flower shop owner.

888
01:06:32,470 --> 01:06:34,950
I feel like I'm in a time machine.

889
01:06:36,900 --> 01:06:39,810
What about college? Did you go?

890
01:06:39,810 --> 01:06:41,670
I did.

891
01:06:41,670 --> 01:06:46,320
I had to get a scholarship.

892
01:06:46,320 --> 01:06:48,470
But was it my first year, second semester?

893
01:06:48,470 --> 01:06:50,790
I lost my top spot in my department.

894
01:06:50,790 --> 01:06:54,740
Seriously. I really wanted to kill.

895
01:06:55,900 --> 01:07:00,900
I even wondered if I'd get it if I did...

896
01:07:03,060 --> 01:07:04,990
Isn't that funny?

897
01:07:12,650 --> 01:07:15,060
Hey, are you okay?

898
01:07:15,060 --> 01:07:17,820
Yeah. I'm fine.

899
01:07:17,820 --> 01:07:20,320
She can't hold her liquor.

900
01:07:20,320 --> 01:07:22,720
She can walk on two feet, right?

901
01:07:22,720 --> 01:07:26,110
I didn't even get to talk to her that much.

902
01:07:29,170 --> 01:07:30,810
Thanks.

903
01:07:40,790 --> 01:07:42,800
What?

904
01:07:42,800 --> 01:07:44,560
I'm moving.

905
01:07:45,350 --> 01:07:46,990
But why?

906
01:07:48,020 --> 01:07:49,960
You should pay me.

907
01:07:51,260 --> 01:07:53,360
Am I on your back?

908
01:07:54,570 --> 01:07:57,840
I let you drink too much by yourself.

909
01:07:57,840 --> 01:07:59,880
Are you okay?

910
01:07:59,880 --> 01:08:01,990
No, I'm not.

911
01:08:01,990 --> 01:08:03,440
You're not?

912
01:08:03,440 --> 01:08:05,220
I'm fine.

913
01:08:06,270 --> 01:08:07,960
Let's get down.

914
01:08:09,130 --> 01:08:12,290
Aren't I light as a feather?

915
01:08:15,280 --> 01:08:18,350
This is just until the taxi stand.

916
01:08:19,350 --> 01:08:22,470
I feel so drunk.

917
01:08:24,270 --> 01:08:28,040
 

918
01:08:31,970 --> 01:08:34,120
Careful.

919
01:08:39,600 --> 01:08:42,800
Let me go get a hangover drink.
Stay here for one second.

920
01:08:43,880 --> 01:08:46,040
Is there a convenience store around here?

921
01:08:50,070 --> 01:08:55,390
I think I missed you once.

922
01:08:59,600 --> 01:09:02,540
I think I was curious.

923
01:09:04,310 --> 01:09:07,580
You disappeared without a trace.

924
01:09:07,580 --> 01:09:11,710
I wondered how you were doing.

925
01:09:12,950 --> 01:09:14,920
How would I disappear without a trace?

926
01:09:14,920 --> 01:09:17,070
Are you a poet?

927
01:09:17,070 --> 01:09:21,610
All the paths you turned your back on

928
01:09:23,170 --> 01:09:26,750
were all so dark.

929
01:09:32,790 --> 01:09:34,420
I think I'm drunk.

930
01:09:34,420 --> 01:09:38,610
All these feelings are coming.

931
01:09:50,920 --> 01:09:53,070
I was curious, too.

932
01:09:54,750 --> 01:09:57,200
Whether you'd be in college

933
01:09:57,200 --> 01:10:00,370
or become one of the things your mom wrote down.

934
01:10:01,300 --> 01:10:05,720
I wondered if we'd see each other again,
no matter what you became.

935
01:10:06,780 --> 01:10:08,400
Stuff like that.

936
01:10:20,650 --> 01:10:22,220
Should we?

937
01:10:23,910 --> 01:10:25,300
What?

938
01:10:27,320 --> 01:10:29,780
The thing your actress is in.

939
01:10:33,320 --> 01:10:36,120
- Why?
- Well...

940
01:10:37,300 --> 01:10:41,100
if I go on TV and helps the flower
shop, I'll make a lot of money.

941
01:10:43,420 --> 01:10:45,380
My career aspiration...

942
01:10:46,960 --> 01:10:48,510
was to be rich.

943
01:11:05,710 --> 01:11:11,350
 ♫ Come closer ♫ 

944
01:11:11,350 --> 01:11:18,260
 ♫ The red sunset ♫ 

945
01:11:18,260 --> 01:11:25,220
 ♫ Night and day meet briefly ♫ 

946
01:11:25,220 --> 01:11:31,390
 ♫ Like us back then ♫ 

947
01:11:33,440 --> 01:11:39,140
 ♫ Like falling asleep ♫ 

948
01:11:39,140 --> 01:11:48,330
 ♫ Pretending not to know and embrace ♫ 

949
01:11:48,330 --> 01:11:55,230
 ♫ It's like love that gets pushed away ♫ 

950
01:11:55,230 --> 01:12:02,270
 ♫ Like the longing that comes back ♫ 

951
01:12:02,270 --> 01:12:11,840
 ♫ Like the horizon where day and night meet ♫ 

952
01:12:17,200 --> 01:12:22,880
 It would be a lie if I said
I never thought about you. 

953
01:12:22,880 --> 01:12:26,420
 It wasn't that dark, thanks to you. 

954
01:12:26,420 --> 01:12:28,480
 Is that what she was asking about? 

955
01:12:28,480 --> 01:12:29,800
 A new start. 

956
01:12:29,800 --> 01:12:33,340
 I'm determined to get along
with you until the shoot is over. 

957
01:12:33,340 --> 01:12:34,380
 That's Sunwoo Hae! 

958
01:12:34,380 --> 01:12:35,940
 What happened? 

959
01:12:35,940 --> 01:12:37,680
 - What?
-Hey, Bebop. 

960
01:12:37,680 --> 01:12:38,890
 Hey, Beat. 

961
01:12:38,890 --> 01:12:41,250
 Do you feel awkward around me? 

962
01:12:41,250 --> 01:12:43,800
 No. Not at all. Why would I? 

963
01:12:44,780 --> 01:12:48,740
 Isn't Sunwoo Hae's story
so ripe for tearing apart? 

964
01:12:48,740 --> 01:12:54,960
 Hey, Sunwoo Hae. Why did you agree to do this? 

965
01:12:54,960 --> 01:12:57,000
 What happens to us now? 

966
01:12:57,000 --> 01:13:07,100
 ♫ Some memories lean on me
like they're happy to see me ♫ 

